  "text": "The chronic model consisted of a sensitization regimen identical to that described for the acute model, with a prolonged, but less severe, challenge period. On day 14, mice were randomized to repeated exposure to nebulized 2.5% OVA in PBS or PBS alone for 2 consecutive days (25 min/day) every 2 wk up to week 12 (i.e., 2 consecutive days of exposure followed by 12 days of rest between exposures) [CITATION_1] .",
